Empty caption bars sometimes appear in certain parts of the timeline after multiple edits are made to the captions.
This usually happens when the caption has been edited several times.










In some parts, captions also overlap with each other, which makes them difficult to adjust.

There is no “auto-snapping” feature, so even a small mistake, especially when using “Undo”, can easily mess up the captions.












































We would like to have an auto-snapping feature (like capcut) for both captions and visuals so they can be aligned more quickly and we can avoid black screens and glitches in clips and captions.
And this would ensure that captions are properly synchronized with the visuals.













Adding an option like this would be very helpful, especially for applying changes to all captions at once.
For example, if you want to center all captions or apply the same X and Y position, you wouldn’t need to adjust each caption individually.



























































I think it would also be better if there were customizable shortcut keys like capcut, since this is one of the factors that helps speed up editing.

Also, some basic shortcut keys are not working consistently, such as “Ctrl + C” for copy and “Ctrl + V” for pasting.



































